About this listing

The Davis Room has 2 twin beds which is perfect for couples, traveling friends, and family. It is a 6 minute walk to Davis Square which is full of coffee shops, restaurants, bars, and shops with access to the red line at the Davis Square T Stop.

Contact Host

Cute twin beds with your personalized goodie basket, mints, and fresh towels. Also, an up close view of our families vintage Beatles poster

Description

The Space

Freshly painted bedroom, living room, hallway and foyer. We have talented Interior Designers in the family! :)

This funky room is one of two Airbnb listings in our large apartment. You may get a chance to meet some of our other wonderful guests! Our 3rd floor apartment is more than just a place to stay, it's a place to relax, laugh and enjoy yourself. With a fully stocked bar (and a fully experienced bartender to prepare something for you) we encourage you to ask questions about the area and Boston in general. Your room will have two beds (can be pushed together or separate), and a desk if you need to work. There's also a large closet to hang up your travel clothes.

This is one of two listings that we have on airbmb

Guest Access

BAR: You will also have access to our now World Famous Fish Tank Bar, if you would like a drink or two!

SHARED AREAS: Living room, kitchen, and bathroom are all shared spaces. We have flexible schedules, so our shower time is usually in the afternoon/evening creating no conflicts. :)

PARKING: There is guest parking right on our street (not a specific spot) for you.

INTERNET: Wireless internet is available throughout the apartment and we have Netflix if you feel like a night on the couch.

Interaction with Guests

We try to always be there for our guests arrival and love to spend time with them, but we both have busy schedules and work into the night occasionally. Bryan has lived in this apartment for 9 years so he has great suggestions for bars, restaurants and places to see. And of course, he'll be more than happy to make you a nicely crafted cocktail after a long day!

The Neighborhood

It's a wonderful neighborhood of mostly families on a quiet tree-lined street. There are tennis and basketball courts a short walk away as well as a great market for fresh produce and craft beer.

Getting Around

Very easy access to both the bus lines (main routes run into Harvard Square) and the Red Line on the T (Davis Square stop is a 6 minute walk/ Porter Square is a 10 minute walk)

Other Things to Note

Davis Square is a great area to go explore with tons of restaurants and bars and is a 6 minute walk from the apartment. Definitely worth checking out!

+ More
House Rules

Our apartment does not allow pets. Smokers are allowed, but there is NO smoking inside the apartment. Please use the back deck. Of course we would ask that you treat fellow guests and hosts with the same level of respect that you deserve. :)

Michael

I had a great experience with Bryan and Marissa! The neighborhood was great; a short walk to Harvard made browsing around the campus a breeze. Marissa was very helpful and such a nice person. She gave a great restaurant recommendation to "The Painted Burro" in nearby Somerville, where I enjoyed one of the most wonderful meals I have ever had. The Burro had great food and drink, plus a service staff that went way beyond expectations. Also had great conversation with a fellow guest who was staying during her Boston stop in a national touring company of a Broadway show. My stay was truly a pleasure!

Loved the location and how close it was to the the metro station. The neighborhood was quaint and quiet and very New England! We enjoyed all the different little decorations as they told a story about the couple and where they come from and where they have traveled. The room was comfortable with plenty of room to walk around and store your luggage. We enjoyed talking to fellow AirBnB hosts and loved every local craft beer place Brian recommended. They are a great laid back couple who I wish the best of luck in the future adventures and endeavors!

The pictures are edited to make the apartment look brighter and cleaner but overall it was a good stay. I did not meet Marisa but I'm assuming she is who sends messages and she would check in on us to make sure we had everything we needed. The welcome basket, towel and extra toiletries were a nice touch. The room would get a little warm but eventually the a/c would cool it down. Good hosts, great location. You can tell they have been hosting for awhile because they have a good system setup for the guests.

September 2015
Melissa

I didn't meet my hosts, Bryan and Marisa but they made sure I had everything I needed for a comfortable stay. They gave me their cell number and responded quickly to messages I left on Airbnb. They left a basket with some goodies and several reference books and maps for things to do in Boston and Cambridge. They provide a high quality soft towel as well as shampoo and conditioner. The apartment was charming and decorated in a fun way, exactly like the pictures. The twin bed had a traditional "bouncy" mattress but I was comfortable anyway. The weather was very warm (mid-September) and the apartment was hot but there was an air conditioner in my room. Cambridge is one of the most charming, clean, and beautiful places I've visited. I walked around Cambridge and Harvard University which is breath-taking. I also found some great vegan restaurants. Everyone I met was very friendly and I received great service everywhere I went. Cambridge has bike lanes throughout the town and although there are a lot of cyclists, there was a lot of car traffic as well. It's a great city to walk around. Parking is limited but Bryan and Marisa provided a visitor's parking pass so I can park on their street. Cambridge reminds me of a very clean Greenpoint, Brooklyn, NY for a frame of reference. Unfortunately I didn't get a chance to visit Boston since I only stayed the weekend. I plan to go back and I definitely will stay in the apartment again. Thank you, Bryan and Marisa!

About the Host, Bryan & Marisa

Hello!
Bryan and Marisa met while Marisa was an AirBnb host in Flordia, the two stayed in touch over a year and now are happy to be hosting together up in Boston!
We are also frequent AirBnb guests during our traveling adventures. Bryan being a professional bartender, and Marisa being a professional Vegan, you can always be sure there is something interesting to eat and drink around our apartment!

We're the best, book with us! ;)
